reviews.headline: A Happy Lanc√¥me Matte Fan
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This foundation feels so good on my skin. I put it on after allowing my moisturizer to dry and I was so surprised how well it blended into my skin since I never have good results with foundation matching. But Lancome said we got you! They have a diverse range of shades and coverage to match my darker skin. This gave me such smooth effortless coverage, I didn't need any blending, any powder, any blush ‚Äì nothing else. I put this foundation on in the morning and wear it all day, it stays looking effortless all day. It has a light scent that fades once it dries and the product dries quickly. I also love that sunscreen is also right in the product, so I don't have to apply a separate sunscreen before applying foundation and then risking my skin feeling oily or sweaty in the Southern heat. Best of all, this foundation is well-suited to all day wear, it minimizes my pores and causes no irritation. Even though I wore this foundation on days when it has been over 100 degrees Fahrenheit, the product has not sweated off. I have even accidentally fallen asleep with it on and had to get up and wash it off in the middle of the night, and still my skin was smooth and breakout free.

reviews.headline: I keep coming back to this one
reviews.comments: As I have gotten older, my foundation needs have changed.  I have tried other brands, but keep coming back to this one.  It goes on smooth, the color match is phenomenal, and the sunscreen is necessary for a foundation product.  I want a dewy product that does not end up looking cakey and this one delivers.  It's a little pricey, but worth it.

reviews.headline: Love it!
reviews.comments: I've been shopping around for a liquid foundation that would work well for my mature skin.  It's my first time to try this foundation, and I absolutely love it!  I like that it has sunscreen protection.  Doesn't feel cakey or too thick.  Full coverage as it states; I did not have to have to use a concealer for some medium dark spots on my cheeks.  Lasted great through a 5 hour round of golf, in very warm and somewhat humid weather.  I'm so glad I found the perfect match for my skin and its needs.

media.headline: Waterproof, All Day Wear, Breathable Foundation from Lanc√¥me
media.caption:
Review of Lanc√¥me Teint Idole Ultra Wear Foundation 110C

Living in the Southeast it's a challenge wearing makeup in such high humidity ten months out of the year. I'm always looking for makeup that can stand up to such high humidity levels and hot temperatures. This one feels good in the humidity and heat. I didn't notice wearing it like I normally do with other brands. Nor am I anxious to remove it after I return home from being outside. Other brands I have to wash off due to irritation after being outdoors. I love the pump, it dispenses just the right amount. It takes so little that this huge bottle will last a long time. I also like that the bottle is glass and it looks nice on my vanity. It has good coverage. I recommend using a foundation brush to apply it. Also, I recommend adding a primer first so it's easier to blend quickly since it is so concentrated. 110C is the perfect shade for those with fair skin with pink undertones. I recommend you give this foundation a try especially if you need a foundation that will last all day, is breathable, and is waterproof. Lanc√¥me is a brand I enjoy and trust. faceoff_negative.comments: So disappointed with the new formula. I've worn the original formula for over a decade, it was the best coverage. I had high hopes for the new formula, unfortunately after multiple days of wearing it I can say it's a huge disappointment and now after being a loyal Lancome customer I will be looking for a new foundation...so sad. After about 2 hours of wear it looks like it's been on for days, completely settles into fine lines, migrates at the slightest touch throughout the day, and has cause completely unexpected acne breakouts for me and my daughter. This is a complete 180 from the original. I don't know who you used for R and D, but they should be fired. Your marketing for the new formula has been top notch, but that's about it since I've found all the celebrity/influencer reviews and testimony to be completely inaccurate in my personal experience with the product. So bummed I bought 3 bottles with the expectation of loving this one as I did it's predecessor.
faceoff_negative.headline: Terrible New Formula For Long Time Customers
